but%20as%20the%20bus%20pulled%20up%20at%20the%20Promenade%20and%20the%20teen%20tried%20to%20get%20off%2C%20Taylor%20lunged%20at%20her.%C2%A0He%20grabbed%20the%2019-year-old's%20face%20and%20repeatedly%20bit%20her%20nose%20and%20mouth.%20The%20violent%20assault%20lasted%20approximately%20five%20minutes%2C%20leaving%20Ms%20Dowling%20severely%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20help%20of%20her%20friends%2C%20she%20managed%20to%20escape%20and%20bystanders%20held%20Taylor%20until%20the%20police%20arrived.%20He%20was%20arrested%20for%20causing%20grievous%20bodily%20harm%20with%20intent%20after%20leaving%20the%20teen%20student%20severely%20injured.%20Her%C2%A0left%20nostril%20to%20the%20lower%20part%20of%20her%20top%20lip%20was%20detached%2C%20except%20for%20a%20thin%20layer%20of%20skin.%20Her%20lip%20on%20the%20right%20side%20was%20also%20split%20open%20and%20she%20had%20visible%20bite%20marks%20over%20her%20nose%20and%20mouth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20young%20woman%20was%20quickly%20taken%20to%20Cheltenham%20General%20Hospital%20before%20moving%20to%20Gloucestershire%20Royal%20Hospital%20for%20emergency%20surgery.%20She%20required%2050%20stitches%20for%20her%20injuries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202024%2C%20Taylor%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20GBH%20with%20intent%20at%20Gloucester%20Crown%20Court.%20On%20July%2018%2C%20he%20received%20a%20sentence%20of%20six%20years%20and%20nine%20months%20in%20prison%2C%20accompanied%20by%20a%20lifelong%20restraining%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EA%20man%20has%20been%20jailed%20after%20he%20bit%20a%20woman's%20face%20and%20caused%20significant%20injuries%20to%20her.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnDarren%20Taylor%20attacked%20the%2019-year-old%20victim%20on%20a%20bus%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FCheltenham%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Cheltenham%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November%20last%20year%20(2023).%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnMore%20on%20the%20case%20here%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F0WYEbnqmXt%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F0WYEbnqmXt%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F2PHcZU1Kbp%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F2PHcZU1Kbp%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Gloucestershire%20Constabulary%20(%40Glos_Police)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FGlos_Police%2Fstatus%2F1821901770844487798%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%209%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElla%2C%20a%20social%20work%20student%20at%20Portsmouth%20University%20from%20Cheltenham%2C%20Gloucestershire%2C%20said%2C%20''The%20pain%20I%20felt%20when%20he%20sank%20his%20teeth%20into%20my%20face%20is%20something%20which%20will%20stay%20with%20me%20forever.%20He%20was%20like%20a%20dog%20with%20a%20toy%20%E2%80%93%20moving%20his%20head%20side%20to%20side.%20I%20put%20my%20hands%20around%20the%20back%20of%20his%20head%20because%20I%20knew%20if%20I%20didn't%20he%20would%20rip%20my%20lip%20and%20nose%20off%20completely.%20When%20I%20saw%20my%20face%20for%20the%20first%20time%20after%20the%20attack%2C%20I%20didn't%20recognise%20my%20own%20reflection%2C%20and%20I%20couldn't%20look%20in%20the%20mirror%20for%20months%20after%20that.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Dowling%20revealed%20that%20the%20traumatic%20experience%20left%20her%20with%20lasting%20effects.%20She%20hasn't%20taken%20the%20bus%20since%20the%20incident%20due%20to%20her%20post-traumatic%20stress%20disorder%20(PTSD).%20Whenever%20she%20leaves%20her%20house%2C%20she%20requires%20constant%20reassurance%2C%20needing%20to%20be%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20her%20mother%20or%20a%20friend%20due%20to%20an%20intense%20fear%20of%20being%20attacked%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20added%2C%20''People%20say%20my%20scar%20is%20healing%20well%20but%20for%20me%2C%20it's%20more%20than%20a%20scar%2C%20it's%20a%20disfigurement%20and%20a%20