icially%20%E2%80%94%20high%20high%20fueled%20by%20a%20pandemic%20bump%20in%20spending.%20Consumers%20had%20savings%20and%20stimulus%20checks%20and%20nowhere%20to%20go%2C%20so%20they%20spent%20extra%20cash%20on%20bags%2C%20wallets%2C%20and%20the%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20economic%20uncertainty%20has%20affected%20countries%20worldwide%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-luxury-slump-stimulus-measures-lvmh-revenue-earnings-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20property%20crisis%20and%20high%20youth%20unemployment%20rates%20in%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20biggest%20luxury%20markets%2C%20have%20hit%20the%20region%20particularly%20hard.%20LVMH%20sales%20in%20Asia%2C%20excluding%20Japan%2C%20fell%2016%25%20year-over-year%20for%20the%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsumer%20confidence%20in%20mainland%20China%20today%20is%20back%20in%20line%20with%20the%20all-time%20low%20reached%20during%20COVID%2C%26quot%3B%20LVMH's%20chief%20financial%20officer%2C%20Jean-Jacques%20Guiony%2C%20told%20analysts%20during%20its%20earnings%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20it's%20too%20early%20to%20tell%20if%20the%20country's%20stimulus%20package%20or%20the%20recent%20national%20holiday%20would%20boost%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20personal%20luxury%20sales%20in%20China%20grew%20by%20more%20than%2037%25%20each%20year%20from%202019%20through%202021%2C%20that%20annual%20growth%20is%20not%20expected%20to%20hit%20more%20than%204.2%25%20through%202028%2C%20according%20to%20EMARKETER%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a8668278-865b-4731-8ca2-2e215ef67ebd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20brands%20can%20bounce%20back%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20contraction%20in%20luxury%20spending%20may%20not%20have%20had%20to%20be%20as%20sharp%20as%20it%20was%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20macroeconomic%20conditions.%20There%20are%20levers%20that%20brands%20can%20pull%20to%20hamper%