n%20out.%20A%20histopathology%20report%20also%20confirmed%20that%20she%20had%20endometriosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20procedure%2C%20life%20has%20been%20much%20better%20for%20Sneha.%20She%20no%20longer%20has%20to%20pop%20painkillers%20and%20is%20able%20to%20lead%20a%20normal%20life.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20a%20lot%20of%20gaslighting%20and%20insinuating%20that%20I%20was%20clamouring%20for%20attention%2C%20this%20diagnosis%20gave%20me%20the%20validation%20I%20needed.%20I%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20wrong%3B%20I%20knew%20my%20body%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20remarks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Pain%20is%20not%20part%20of%20being%20a%20woman%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20Devleena%2C%20the%20complications%20after%20the%20first%20surgery%20in%20February%202023%20caused%20a%20lot%20of%20pain%2C%20even%20more%20excruciating%20than%20before.%20%E2%80%9CSince%20I%20had%20to%20travel%20a%20lot%20for%20work%2C%20I%20kept%20blaming%20it%20on%20water%20or%20food%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20felt%20like%201%2C000%20needles%20were%20pricking%20me%20from%20the%20inside.%20The%20pain%20was%20so%20sharp%2C%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20stand%3B%20I%20would%20just%20collapse.%20I%20kept%20throwing%20up%2C%20feeling%20anxious%20and%20depressed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20even%20consulted%20another%20gynaecologist%20in%20Delhi%20who%20said%20that%20it%20might%20be%20endometriosis%20and%20asked%20her%20to%20consider%20taking%20birth%20control%20pills.%20%E2%80%9CSince%20the%20doctor%20didn%E2%80%99t%20insist%20much%2C%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20them%20as%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20add%20another%20set%20of%20pills.%20I%20wish%20she%20had%20explained%20to%20me%20how%20it%20would%20help%20my%20situation%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Devleena.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-me